Name: McGraw-Hill's 500 MCAT Physics Questions to Know by Test Day: 3 Reading Tests + 3 Writing Tests + 3 Mathematics Tests (McGraw-Hill's 500 Questions)

ReviewList.Text: It's a decent book, but I've noticed a few mistakes text. For example the wording can be vague, both in questions and in the explained answers. Otherwise, a good book for practice.
I love that it has a bunch of questions related to the physics section of the MCAT because unlike practice exams you get a whole range of topics and you can see where your weaknesses lie
